{
  "text": "From this automatically-annotated corpus we extract the top 10, 000 events and their corresponding dates using the G 2 test, which measures the strength of association between an entity and date using the log-likelihood ratio between a model in which the entity is conditioned on the date and a model of independence [CITATION_1] . Events extracted using this approach then simply consist of the highest-scoring entity-date pairs, for example [Mercury, 5/9/2016] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "207196336"
